    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-14T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-14T13:00:00-05:00" n="326"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/7–1445: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 326<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_KGF1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-14T21:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 14, 1945—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2570. <hi rend="smallcaps">
                        <gloss target="#t_Safehaven1">Safehaven</gloss>
                    </hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> has not rec’d any reply (<gloss
                        target="#t_reDeptel1">ReDeptel</gloss> 1475, June 30<note n="l"
                        xml:id="d326fnl">
                        <ref target="#d325">Document No. 325</ref>.</note>) to its <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">
                        <gloss target="#t_Safehaven1">Safehaven</gloss>
                    </hi> notes to <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> of April 30 (London tel
                    4254, April 26<note n="2" xml:id="d326fn2">Not printed.</note>) and June 18
                        (<gloss target="#t_reEmbtel1">ReEmbtel</gloss> 2169, June 19<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d326fn3">Not printed. This message reported execution of the
                        instructions printed in footnote 1 to <ref target="#d382">document No.
                            382</ref>.</note>) or any indication of desire to discuss matter.</p>
                <p>We believe Russians likely to persist in refusal to assent to general freezing of
                    state as well as private assets unless strong pressure can be brought to bear or
                    arguments adduced more forceful from Russian point of view than fact that
                    general freeze is technically more practicable (sent <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> as 2570 <gloss target="#t_rptd1">rptd</gloss> London as
                    360).</p>
                <p>Russian aim is naturally to obtain for Soviet Govt maximum effective power of
                    disposition over all these assets. Russians wish private assets blocked and
                    placed at disposition of <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss>s because they
                    control all <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss>s and only in this way can they
                    effectively guard against disposal over these assets by private individuals
                    without their knowledge or consent. They do not wish state assets blocked
                    because they effectively control govts in question and are thus able to control
                    all dispositions over these assets. Hence they have a clear material interest in
                    arrangement they have proposed whereby private assets would be blocked and
                    released only on orders of respective <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss>s and
                    state assets would not be blocked at all, and this interest will be uppermost in
                    their minds in any consideration of these questions.</p>
                <p>In view of above <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> would prefer to discuss
                    entire problem with <persName corresp="#p_RSJ1">Rubin</persName> who is expected
                    here shortly before recommending further approach to <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KGF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
